javaslang.algebra

Interface Functor<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - component type of this functor
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Arbitrary<T>, Future<T>, Gen<T>, IndexedSeq<T>, Iterator<T>, Lazy<T>, LinearSeq<T>, List<T>, Map<K,V>, Match.MatchMonad<R>, Monad<T>, Option<T>, Seq<T>, Set<T>, SortedMap<K,V>, SortedSet<T>, Stack<T>, Stream<T>, Traversable<T>, Tree<T>, Try<T>, Value<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Array, CharSeq, Either.LeftProjection, Either.RightProjection, Failure, HashMap, HashSet, Lazy.Defined, Lazy.Undefined, LinkedHashMap, LinkedHashSet, List.Cons, List.Nil, Match.MatchMonad.Otherwise, Match.MatchMonad.When.Then, None, Queue, Some, Stream.Cons, Stream.Empty, Success, Tree.Empty, Tree.Node, TreeMap, TreeSet, Vector

    public interface Functor<T>

    Defines a Functor by generalizing the map.

    All instances of the Functor interface should obey the two functor laws:
    • m.map(a -> a) ≡ m
    • m.map(f.compose(g)) ≡ m.map(g).map(f)
    where "f, g ∈ Function".
    Since:
    1.1.0
    Author:
    Daniel Dietrich
    See Also:
    The functor design pattern
